02:17:58.207 --> 02:18:02.917
It really depended on what was happening
in his life and in his world.

2309
02:18:03.167 --> 02:18:06.716
I had no reason to think
or believe that he was on drugs

2310
02:18:06.847 --> 02:18:09.805
until my children came to me one time
and they said it.

2311
02:18:09.887 --> 02:18:12.685
and I said.
"Well. I've never seen him in that shape."

2312
02:18:12.767 --> 02:18:15.600
Then I went to him
and I talked to him about it.

2313
02:18:15.687 --> 02:18:17.598
and he kept denying it.

2314
02:18:20.727 --> 02:18:24.481
I asked him. I said. "Now. Michael.
is there any problems I should know about?"

2315
02:18:25.207 --> 02:18:26.401
"What do you mean?"

2316
02:18:26.527 --> 02:18:30.042
I said. "Well. you know.
once in a while you seem a little dizzy.

2317
02:18:30.127 --> 02:18:31.321
"You wanna go to rehab?"

2318
02:18:31.607 --> 02:18:36.283
"No. No! There you go. See?
Now. why would you assume that?

2319
02:18:36.407 --> 02:18:40.002
"I'm not taking anything. Frank.
I'm not doing one thing."

2320
02:18:40.887 --> 02:18:42.400
One of the people
working for him said.

2321
02:18:42.487 --> 02:18:45.638
"You won't ever guess
what this man is doing to get to sleep."

2322
02:18:45.727 --> 02:18:46.762
And I said. "What?"

2323
02:18:46.847 --> 02:18:49.077
And I was told he's using an anaesthetic.

2324
02:18:49.167 --> 02:18:51.158
And I said. "What?

2325
02:18:51.647 --> 02:18:55.276
"How do you do that?"
I had never heard of such a thing.

2326
02:18:55.447 --> 02:19:00.043
He said. "Dude. I don't know what to tell you.
but that's what's going on."

2327
02:19:00.287 --> 02:19:05.600
Unfortunately. he did find doctors
who were willing to do this crazy thing

2328
02:19:05.687 --> 02:19:08.121
that ultimately led to his death.

2329
02:19:09.127 --> 02:19:11.436
Fire Paramedic 33.
What is the nature of your emergency?

2330
02:19:11.527 --> 02:19:15.202
We have a gentleman here
that needs help. he's not breathing.

2331
02:19:15.567 --> 02:19:18.240
We have breaking news
for you tonight.

2332
02:19:19.207 --> 02:19:23.644
the singer Michael Jackson
is reported to have died from a heart attack.

2333
02:19:31.687 --> 02:19:35.236
I heard that my brother had passed away
through my sister Janet.

2334
02:19:35.327 --> 02:19:36.362
Tito Jackson
MICHAEL'S BROTHER

2335
02:19:36.447 --> 02:19:39.598
who asked me to pull over
'cause I was rushing over to my mom's.

2336
02:19:41.087 --> 02:19:42.759
I just couldn't believe it.

2337
02:19:44.207 --> 02:19:49.201
So. I had to just sit in my car
and pull myself together.

2338
02:19:49.447 --> 02:19:51.324
you know. and I went over
to my mom's home.

2339
02:19:53.727 --> 02:19:56.525
The entire family had met that evening.

2340
02:19:56.607 --> 02:20:01.556
and was there condoling each other.
you know.

2341
02:20:03.927 --> 02:20:05.155
It was rough.

2342
02:20:05.247 --> 02:20:07.556
Just the whole time
was a rough time in my life.

2343
02:20:08.287 --> 02:20:10.755
Rebbie Jackson
MICHAEL'S SISTER

2344
02:20:10.847 --> 02:20:14.283
It's so very difficult even to talk about it.
It really is.

2345
02:20:22.367 --> 02:20:24.085
I was heartbroken.

2346
02:20:24.967 --> 02:20:27.276
I was just totally heartbroken.

2347
02:20:28.447 --> 02:20:33.475
It was probably one of the most surreal

2348
02:20:33.567 --> 02:20:34.556
Peabo Bryson
SINGER

2349
02:20:34.727 --> 02:20:41.041
and solemn days of life as we know it.
I would think.

2350
02:20:46.287 --> 02:20:48.676
I was devastated. I started to cry.

2351
02:20:48.767 --> 02:20:49.756
David Gest
MICHAEL'S CLOSE FRIEND

2352
02:20:50.647 --> 02:20:56.643
We had spent 40 years of our lives
as the closest of friends.

2353
02:20:57.927 --> 02:20:59.963
And I couldn't believe it.

2354
02:21:00.327 --> 02:21:03.205
I remember the feeling I got. you know.

2355
02:21:03.287 --> 02:21:04.436
Lamont Dozier
SONGWRITER. HOLLAND-DOZIER-HOLLAND

2356
02:21:04.527 --> 02:21:07.087
It was like somebody punching you
in the stomach.

2357
02:21:07.447 --> 02:21:09.403
God. it was just so...

2358
02:21:16.847 --> 02:21:19.122
I didn't follow the news a lot.

2359
02:21:19.767 --> 02:21:21.997
I'll tell you why I didn't follow the news.

2360
02:21:22.087 --> 02:21:23.076
Eddie Floyd
SINGER I SONGWRITER. STAX RECORDS

2361
02:21:23.167 --> 02:21:28.924
It's because of the people
exploiting the man.

2362
02:21:33.087 --> 02:21:34.679
That makes me sad.

2363
02:21:37.247 --> 02:21:39.477
The night that Michael died.

2364
02:21:39.567 --> 02:21:41.717
the next show I did.
I mentioned Michael. too.

2365
02:21:41.807 --> 02:21:42.796
Dennis Edwards
LEAD SINGER. 'THE TEMPTATIONS'

2366
02:21:42.887 --> 02:21:44.605
It just was...

2367
02:21:44.687 --> 02:21:46.882
People just stood up. you know.
They stood up.

2368
02:21:46.967 --> 02:21:49.845
And a lot of people took
their cigarette lighters out

2369
02:21:49.927 --> 02:21:51.246
and just lit it.

2370
02:21:51.647 --> 02:21:55.003
You know. it's just sad. man. It's sad.

2371
02:22:02.567 --> 02:22:04.398
It's just a sad moment.

2372
02:22:04.487 --> 02:22:08.685
to have to carry one of your brothers
to his grave.

2373
02:22:09.367 --> 02:22:13.724
We would perform all night.
tell you the truth. every day.

2374
02:22:13.967 --> 02:22:16.197
It's not a good feeling.

2375
02:22:16.287 --> 02:22:19.279
It's a major part of you died with that.

2376
02:22:21.767 --> 02:22:23.917
And there was this man's house.
who used to sell candy.

2377
02:22:24.007 --> 02:22:28.080
we used to stop there and just load up.
eat candy for days.

2378
02:22:29.607 --> 02:22:31.438
I never lost a child.

2379
02:22:33.287 --> 02:22:37.405
Children are supposed to bury their parents.
not parents bury their children.

2380
02:22:38.007 --> 02:22:40.396
And that's what hurt me the most.

2381
02:22:55.327 --> 02:22:59.923
Many days. I go back to his first cry.

2382
02:23:00.007 --> 02:23:03.044
from the doctor slapping him on his butt.

2383
02:23:03.167 --> 02:23:04.236
up till his death.

2384
02:23:05.567 --> 02:23:06.556
But

2385
02:23:11.567 --> 02:23:17.324
all the memories of Michael are fond to me.
I can't pick out any particular.

2386
02:23:25.487 --> 02:23:27.876
I'm happy with the children here.

2387
02:23:28.087 --> 02:23:31.716
and at the same time.
I'm sad because their father's gone.

2388
02:23:32.207 --> 02:23:35.404
They always say. "Daddy did it this way.

2389
02:23:35.607 --> 02:23:38.644
"Daddy used to do this.
Daddy used to do that."

2390
02:23:40.647 --> 02:23:43.605
Those kids are so proud of their father.

2391
02:23:45.727 --> 02:23:47.558
I can't find words.

2392
02:23:51.127 --> 02:23:53.516
To me. it's just such a loss. too soon.

2393
02:23:53.607 --> 02:23:54.756
Eddie Holland
SONGWRITER. HOLLAND-DOZIER-HOLLAND

2394
02:23:57.127 --> 02:23:58.480
It left such a gap
and made us see what was missing.

2395
02:23:58.567 --> 02:23:59.556
Valerie Simpson & Nickolas Ashford

2396
02:23:59.647 --> 02:24:00.636
SINGERS I SONGWRITERS.
'ASHFORD & SIMPSON'

2397
02:24:00.727 --> 02:24:03.036
Why hadn't we embraced him?
Why hadn't we loved him?

2398
02:24:03.127 --> 02:24:05.687
He gave us so much love

2399
02:24:06.407 --> 02:24:08.602
and so much wonderful music.

2400
02:24:09.367 --> 02:24:12.723
And I think that this is what
we'll always remember him for.

2401
02:24:15.487 --> 02:24:18.763
I love the fact that everything he sang.
he sang from his heart.

2402
02:24:18.847 --> 02:24:22.635
And I love listening to him singing.
every record he's ever recorded.

2403
02:24:24.127 --> 02:24:28.837
Michael's legacy is that he will be known
as the greatest entertainer ever.

2404
02:24:30.087 --> 02:24:31.202
Michael was a great talent.

2405
02:24:31.287 --> 02:24:34.359
He was the best overall talent
that I've ever seen in my life.

2406
02:24:34.447 --> 02:24:36.517
and I've been following talent
since I was three years old.

2407
02:24:38.487 --> 02:24:39.806
He was the best I ever saw.

2408
02:24:42.487 --> 02:24:46.196
I'll remember that little boy that I met
when he was 10 years old.

2409
02:24:46.287 --> 02:24:47.276
Dionne Warwick
SINGER

2410
02:24:47.367 --> 02:24:53.078
that little feisty. cute.
incredibly talented youngster.

2411
02:24:53.727 --> 02:24:59.279
that went on to become one of the greatest
entertainers that ever lived.

2412
02:25:00.727 --> 02:25:02.319
There's only one Michael Jackson.

2413
02:25:05.047 --> 02:25:07.515
To me and my children.

2414
02:25:07.607 --> 02:25:08.642
Percy Sledge
SINGER

2415
02:25:08.727 --> 02:25:10.319
he meant so much to our lives.

2416
02:25:12.087 --> 02:25:15.443
He was. to me. the greatest entertainer
I had ever seen in my life.

2417
02:25:15.527 --> 02:25:16.676
Whitney Houston
SINGER

2418
02:25:16.807 --> 02:25:19.605
He was a gentleman and he was very kind.

2419
02:25:20.287 --> 02:25:22.642
And I'll always love him. always.

2420
02:25:24.847 --> 02:25:26.917
He was one of the warmest

2421
02:25:27.007 --> 02:25:30.397
and most loveable persons
you could ever meet.

2422
02:25:32.727 --> 02:25:36.163
I think Michael's greatest achievement.
throughout his life.

2423
02:25:37.247 --> 02:25:39.238
was making people happy.

2424
02:25:39.327 --> 02:25:40.840
helping people.

2425
02:25:40.967 --> 02:25:45.563
If somebody needed an operation.
or a family starving that needed food.

2426
02:25:45.647 --> 02:25:48.764
he would send over groceries for a year
and things like that.

2427
02:25:49.087 --> 02:25:51.806
I think that's where
he really got his enjoyment.

2428
02:25:52.007 --> 02:25:55.841
seeing somebody sad become happy.

2429
02:25:55.967 --> 02:26:00.006
Those are the things he really wanted
to achieve that was beyond the music.

2430
02:26:00.967 --> 02:26:05.802
We will remember him
as this great showman and humanitarian.

2431
02:26:11.367 --> 02:26:12.482
When people say to me.

2432
02:26:12.567 --> 02:26:14.444
"Do you think of Michael
as being a tragedy?"

2433
02:26:14.527 --> 02:26:16.199
I just don't think of that at all.

2434
02:26:16.327 --> 02:26:19.444
I think that Michael's story
is one of triumph.

2435
02:26:20.607 --> 02:26:24.759
This is a man who was the total embodiment
of the American dream.

2436
02:26:24.847 --> 02:26:29.796
This is a guy who came out of Gary. Indiana.
and set the world on fire.

2437
02:26:30.047 --> 02:26:31.765
He did amazing things with his life.

2438
02:26:31.967 --> 02:26:33.605
Did he make mistakes? Yes.

2439
02:26:33.727 --> 02:26:37.117
But that's the humanity of Michael Jackson.
I think. that's most appealing.

2440
02:26:37.487 --> 02:26:40.001
He wanted to make the world
a better place.

2441
02:26:40.327 --> 02:26:43.364
That spirit of his is still around now.

2442
02:26:43.927 --> 02:26:48.762
The part that I loved the most about him
was that gentle friend side.

2443
02:26:49.047 --> 02:26:51.356
All the other things. everybody knows about.

2444
02:26:51.527 --> 02:26:54.087
But that part of Michael.
that's the part I love.

2445
02:26:54.647 --> 02:26:56.080
God bless Michael Jackson. you know.
'cause he was one of the greatest.

2446
02:26:56.207 --> 02:26:57.196
Kenny Gamble & Leon Huff

2447
02:26:57.287 --> 02:26:58.402
PRODUCERS I SONGWRITERS.
PHILADELPHIA INT. RECORDS

2448
02:27:00.367 --> 02:27:05.760
Michael Jackson became
the biggest pop star of all time

2449
02:27:06.647 --> 02:27:09.480
but that's not how I'm gonna remember him.

2450
02:27:09.687 --> 02:27:12.804
because he was just one great human being.

2451
02:27:14.527 --> 02:27:17.485
Rest well. my friend. I love you. M.

2452
02:27:18.767 --> 02:27:24.080
Katherine. how do you feel
Michael Jackson will be remembered?

2453
02:27:25.167 --> 02:27:29.843
Well. David. Michael practised one thing.
and it was from his heart.

2454
02:27:30.607 --> 02:27:32.723
L-O-V-E. love.

2455
02:27:33.567 --> 02:27:37.719
And I think he will be remembered
for the love that he had for the world.

2456
02:27:37.807 --> 02:27:39.399
and especially for his fans.

2457
02:27:40.167 --> 02:27:41.839
and his family.

2458
02:27:42.367 --> 02:27:43.959
- Thank you so much.
- Okay.

2459
02:27:44.047 --> 02:27:47.039
- I love you. Can I have a big hug?
- Of course.

2460
02:27:48.786 --> 02:27:58.786
